post_text: There seems to be some misinformation out there about protocol for when a student becomes sick this fall at Farwell. Hopefully, I can clear things up a bit. If a student becomes sick or symptomatic at school, they will be taken to an illness isolation room until they can be picked up by a parent or guardian. This is NOT a quarantine! This is really not much different than any other time a student were to come to the office presenting a fever/cough/symptoms. However, instead of sitting in a waiting room in the office that is potentially full of other people, they will be directed to an "isolation" room where they will not be around others. They will NOT be left unattended or unsupervised, and they will NOT be under quarantine. Any decisions to quarantine students will come from the local health department, not FAS.

I know all our Farwell families are anxious for an update about returning to school in the fall. Please be patient, as we try to work out the details. Administrators, teachers, and staff are all asking many of the same questions as you are! We are using the Governor‚Äôs Return to Learn Plan as a starting point for this fall. We are working closely with our local Health Department, the Clare-Gladwin RESD, and the schools in our region to develop a plan that focuses on the safety of students and staff as our first priority. Education and Flexibility will also be key tenants to our plan. We hope to have our plan approved by our Board of Education and published by early August. I am attaching a link of a survey for parents, I welcome your input regarding your child‚Äôs education in the 2020-2021 school year https://forms.gle/UtWr9FPgAybM7uer9.

Please complete the survey to help us determine our best path forward. -Superintendent Scoville

post_text:
Farwell teachers and staff have been hard at work this week preparing for alternate student learning!

Families of elementary students: Packets will be available for pickup tomorrow, April 9th, 2020, from 3-6PM at the Elementary office. Only one adult should come in the building. Please practice social distancing, and don't come in if you are sick. If you receive our meal deliveries, the packets will come to you tomorrow with the regular delivery.

Middle and High School students should be checking their @stu.farwellschools.net email address for instructions and Google Classroom updates. If you don't know how to login to your email, your teacher can help you. Teachers and staff will be contacting students via the phone number listed in Skyward.

We've had a nice, long spring break, but it's time to get back to learning. Online learning will begin April 13th.

Most importantly, please be patient as this is new for all of us. There will likely be bumps along this new road, but like it's been said many times before, "We're all in this together." Let's do this, Eagles!

Farwell is doing everything within our resources to help our families during this time of unprecedented school closure. Below is some information on our food distribution plan:

Beginning on Tuesday, 3-17-2020, Farwell Area Schools will run a school bus food delivery program. These deliveries will be on Tuesdays and Thursdays for the at least the next three weeks, and may be extended if needed. They will include multiple meals.

Our buses will depart for their normal run beginning at 11:00 a.m. Your food delivery time will be approximately 5 hours later than your normal morning pick up time.

One family member may pick up meals for all members of the family 18 and under. We will also include some educational resources with each delivery. We will also have links to educational resources loaded to our Facebook page and the district's website.

We will still offer pick up at the Farwell Area Schools from 3:00 pm ‚Äì 6:00 pm at the JPAC 'Bubble' entrance.

Anyone not wanting a food delivery can contact our transportation department at 989-588-9111.

The MHSAA has directed all member schools to suspend activities in all sports for all seasons - effective Monday, March 16 through at least Sunday, April 5 to fall in line with Gov. Gretchen Whitmer‚Äôs order that all schools close for the next three weeks in order to deter the spread of COVID-19.

FAS has suspended all athletic activities effective Friday, March 13. All athletic activities include practices, scrimmages, competitions, conditioning and strength training for all in-season and out-of-season sports.

We sincerely appreciate your understanding and cooperation during this time.

MHSAA
March 12 at 2:07 PM ¬∑

COVID-19 UPDATE (3/12 - 10 a.m.): Postseason events sponsored by the Michigan High School Athletic Association and scheduled for March 12-14 will be conducted as scheduled. However, attendance will be restricted at all events through this weekend, with updates to be announced Monday, March 16, for the remainder of the girls and boys basketball tournaments.

The MHSAA Ice Hockey Semifinals and Finals will be played March 12-14 at USA Hockey Arena, with Lower Peninsula Boys Swimming & Diving Finals beginning Friday, March 13 and concluding March 14 at Oakland University and Holland Aquatic Center. Girls Gymnastics at Rockford High School also will be competed Friday and Saturday this weekend. Girls Basketball Regionals Finals are scheduled for tonight, March 12, across the state, as are Boys District Finals on Friday, March 13.

Complete Information and Updates can be found by following this page: https://www.mhsaa.com/coronavirus

post_text: The Farwell Area Schools Transportation Department will be accepting bids on a used 2002 Ford Cargo Van. The van has a 5.4 liter V-8 engine with 28,066 miles on it. For more information on the bid process, please contact us at 989-588-9111.

post_text: At last night's school board meeting, we were able to celebrate several people, and it was wonderful! October is Principals' Month, so Mr. Scoville presented a certificate to Dr. Yarger, Mrs. Cairnduff, and Ms. Gross. We also celebrated Kyle Frost, who earned the honor of Eagle Scout. Also featured are FHS Students of the Month: Bishop Wilson, Kylee Donelson, Kaleb Dunford, Thomas Taylor, and Madison Forfinski (not pictured). We love celebrating our Eagles!
